Description:
About the business
Jenike & Johanson (Jenike) is recognized as the world’s leading authority for reliable and efficient bulk solids handling and processing. We have an international clientele that includes many Fortune 100 companies from industries including: chemicals, cement, mining, minerals, foods, power/energy, plastics, and pharmaceuticals.
Our company is 100% owned, with locations in the United States, Canada, South America, and Australia. Such diversification provides for an interesting and rewarding career, developing unique, cost-effective solutions to a wide range of engineering challenges in the world.
About the role
Main duty is determination of flow and particle properties of a wide range of bulk solids:
Managing inward and forward samples;
Sample preparation;
Perform various bulk solid testing as per J&J’s Standard Operating Procedures (SOP);
Provide feedback to lab manager and engineers regarding any issues encountered during testing;
General laboratory housekeeping duties.
Benefits and perks
A rare opportunity for an early career engineer to join one of the world’s great science-based consultancies offering:
Opportunity to grow into world-class expert in bulk material testing;
Small team environment;
Teaching and application ecosystem;
Comprehensive training plan;
A benefits package, including profit sharing, extended health care (prescriptions, dental), LTD, critical illness and life insurance coverage.
Requirements/Qualifications
Only those who meet all selection criteria below will be considered for this important role.
Education:
minimum high school diploma is required, degree or diploma (or equivalent) in mechanical related field is preferred;
Experience:
minimum 2 years of relevant work experience required;
Computer software skills using Office (e.g. Word, Excel), email and messaging and have capacity to learn specialized software for data entry/analysis;
Ability to lift weights 30-40 lb. regularly, up to 50 lb. (23 kg) occasionally;
Physically able to wear a respirator when warranted. Respirator and training will be provided;
Strong attention to detail;
Ability to perform routine bench tests;
Good communication skills in English;
Have strong learning desire and initiative;
Skilled with hardware tools and electrical equipment;
Team player.
Additional preferred qualifications: Canadian driver’s license
If you feel that you are a strong candidate and can demonstrate that you would be a “good fit” for the lab technician position
in Toronto, Canada
, please email your resume and cover letter to “Recruiting department” at Jobs_Toronto@jenike.com .
